Grid overflow on mobile is usually caused by fixed-width columns. Here's the fix:

```css
/* Problem: fixed 3 columns on all screens */
.grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr); gap: 16px; }

/* Fix: stack on mobile */
@media (max-width: 768px) {
  .grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
}

/* Even better: auto-responsive without media queries */
.grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(280px, 1fr)); gap: 16px; }
```

Also check for:
- Fixed pixel widths on cards (use `width: 100%` or `max-width`)
- Missing `<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">` in `<head>`
- Horizontal overflow from pre-formatted text or long URLs (add `overflow-wrap: break-word`)
